[10/21, 7:48 PM] Ruthika: DNS Forwarder: A DNS forwarder is like a smart assistant in the network. When a computer doesn’t know the answer to a DNS query, the forwarder steps in, sending the request to another DNS server and then saving the answer for future requests. This speeds things up and takes the load off your local DNS server
